programme.title: NFL Playoff: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.sub-title: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.desc: New Orleans Saints (12-5) at Minnesota Vikings (13-3) in an NFC Divisional game. From U.S. Bank Stadium. Mike Zimmer's Vikings opened 2017 with a 29-19 win over New Orleans, keeping QB Drew Brees and Co. out of the end zone until the last two minutes. Everson Griffen and Xavier Rhodes head Minnesota's defense, while the Saints boast a Pro Bowl RB tandem in Alvin Kamara and Mark Ingram. The Vikes' last playoff win was eight years ago, followed by an NFC title-game loss to the Saints. (cc)

programme.title: Thursday Night Football: Los Angeles Rams at San Francisco 49ers
programme.sub-title: Los Angeles Rams at San Francisco 49ers
programme.desc: Los Angeles Rams (1-1) at San Francisco 49ers (0-2). From Levi's Stadium. New coaches Sean McVay and Kyle Shanahan open a new chapter in this NFC West series, which the Niners swept for their only two wins of 2016. RBs Todd Gurley and Carlos Hyde star. (cc)

programme.title: NFL Football: Washington Redskins at Seattle Seahawks
programme.desc: Washington Redskins (3-4) at Seattle Seahawks (5-2). From CenturyLink Field. The Redskins (allowing 25.7 ppg) will look to stop a streaking Russell Wilson, who tossed 4 TDs and a career-high 452 yards last week in a thrilling win over the Texans. (cc)

programme.title: NFL Football: Minnesota Vikings at Carolina Panthers
programme.desc: Minnesota Vikings (10-2) at Carolina Panthers (8-4). From Bank of America Stadium. The Vikings can clinch their second NFC North title in three years with a victory in Charlotte, where they rallied to win 22-10 last year, with eight sacks of Cam Newton. (cc)

programme.desc: Few people are aware that John Wayne collaborated with Jim Sullivan to design a .22 rimfire semi-auto rifle. We review Black Hills' .380 ACP, 9mm, .40 S&W, .45 ACP ammo and fire an anti-tank 75mm PAC.(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.sub-title: Hot Times on Ice & Open Water
programme.desc: The staff slides into seasonal slay-them mode as they sample some of the world's finest pike fishing, ride the rising tide of popularity of ice fishing for whitefish, and head to north Texas for warm-water largemouths.(n)

programme.title: On the Water with Hank Parker
programme.desc: Hank Parker and friend Daniel Morgan fish Lake Chickamauga.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: G.O. Heath takes advantage of Kentucky's October muzzleloader season; James Kroll explores the impact of changing demographics on our whitetail hunting heritage; and Stan Potts discusses calling strategies.(n)

programme.title: The Jackie Bushman Show Classics *
programme.desc: Matt and Chipper join Jackie to talk about hunting the bruisers of Kansas. Also: Jimmy Crochet hunts late-season, muzzleloader bucks in Alabama.(n)

programme.title: Respect the Game TV
programme.desc: Part 1. A crowd pleasure from last season, the crew heads back to Montana to hunt with Phillp Vanderpool and the Virtue crew. Powder River here we come.(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted
